    tone="navy"
  />

  <h2>Preparing for winter in Wesley Chapel</h2>
  <p>The single most valuable thing you can do each fall is simple, and it prevents the worst-timed failures:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Run your heater 15 minutes in October.</strong> A brief burning smell is just dust on the strips and is normal.</li>
    <li><strong>Watch for warning signs:</strong> cool air, a lingering burnt smell, tripped breakers, or no airflow all mean call now.</li>
    <li><strong>Book the fall tune-up early,</strong> because our schedule packs the night the first cold snap hits.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>A fall tune-up in October is vastly cheaper than an emergency call the night it hits freezing, and when no-heat turns urgent we treat it like any <a href="/services/emergency-ac-repair-tampa/">emergency</a> and prioritize homes with no working system.</p>

  <OwnerTip>
    <p>"Every January we get a wave of 'my heat smells like burning' calls on the first truly cold night. Most of the time it is just dust burning off heat strips that have not run since last winter, completely normal. But if it lingers, or you get cool air instead of warm, that is a real fault. Run the heat for 15 minutes in October so you find out in mild weather, not at 2am when it is 32 degrees, the same logic behind a spring <a href="/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/">AC tune-up</a>."</p>
  </OwnerTip>

  <h2>Repair or replace your heat pump for better heating?</h2>
  <p>If your heating is weak and the system is aging, the same repair-versus-replace math that applies to cooling applies here:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Repair</strong> when the unit is under 10 years old and the fix is a reversing valve, board, or sensor, which our <a href="/services/ac-repair-tampa/">repair</a> team handles same-day when parts are on the truck.</li>
    <li><strong>Replace</strong> when an old single-stage unit leans on its heat strips all winter, since a modern variable-speed heat pump can cut winter heating costs 30 to 50%.</li>
    <li><strong>Upgrade the controls too,</strong> because a smart thermostat with proper strip lockouts is what keeps a new system from wasting that efficiency.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We show you the numbers both ways through our <a href="/services/ac-replacement-tampa/">replacement</a> process so the decision is yours, not a sales pitch.</p>

  <h2>Heating a Florida room, garage, or addition</h2>
  <p>For spaces your main system does not reach, a dedicated solution beats overworking the central unit:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Ductless mini-splits</strong> heat and cool independently, run 22+ SEER2, and shrug off Tampa winters; see our <a href="/services/mini-split-installation-tampa/">mini-split installation</a> page.</li>
    <li><strong>No heat strips to misfire,</strong> so a converted garage stays comfortable without a January bill spike.</li>
    <li><strong>One quiet unit</strong> for year-round comfort, common in <a href="/service-areas/lutz-home-air-conditioning-service/">Lutz</a> bonus rooms and Florida rooms.</li>
  </ul>

